cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO 

The paper deals with pixel-wise image labeling, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a deep neural network architecture for improving label estimates, which involves detecting incorrect labels, replacing them with new ones, and refining the renewed labels. This suggests that the paper may also belong to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which are related to deep learning and neural networks. Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed architecture on the task of dense disparity estimation (stereo matching), which involves robotics and perception, suggesting that it may also belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category.
